offset_left = 19.0
offset_top = 6283.0
offset_right = 391.0
offset_bottom = 6330.0
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 9: The Doctrine of Inherent Gaseous Consequences[/b][br]The V.T.M. acknowledges and accepts full, sole, and irrevocable responsibility for all gaseous emissions, visible or otherwise, sonic or silent, that may arise from the contemplation, consumption, or mere proximity to beans or bean-derived products, and the G.S.S.L. shall not be held liable for any social ostracization, temporary workplace evacuation, or minor structural damage to nearby windows that may result from the V.T.M.'s digestive processes, and this clause specifically mandates that the V.T.M. must mentally recite the chemical formula for Methane (CH4​) three times before any attempt to blame their emissions on a third party, such as a fictional roommate or a passing squirrel, and this entire legal framework is constructed around the central comedic concept that the V.T.M. has just wasted an entire, precious minute reading a paragraph dedicated entirely to flatulence and its legal ramifications within a document that purports to be the terms of service for a simple captcha game, thereby achieving peak absurdity and optimal temporal depletion, which is, again, the ultimate metric of success for this entire agreement. "
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false
shortcut_keys_enabled = false

[node name="_Control_25" type="Control" parent="ScrollContainer/VBoxContainer"]
layout_mode = 2

[node name="TosArticle" type="RichTextLabel" parent="ScrollContainer/VBoxContainer/_Control_25"]
self_modulate = Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
show_behind_parent = true
layout_mode = 0
offset_left = 19.0
offset_top = 6942.0
offset_right = 391.0
offset_bottom = 6989.0
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 10: Prohibition on Bean-Based Time Travel (B.B.T.T.)[/b][br]The V.T.M. is strictly prohibited from using any bean, bean container, or bean-related recipe as a conduit, catalyst, or component for the construction or operation of a time travel device (B.B.T.T.), even if the bean in question is a hypothetical \"Chronobean\" capable of existing in multiple historical epochs simultaneously, as the resulting paradoxes, particularly concerning whether a bean consumed in the past would affect the V.T.M.'s present-day gaseous output, are deemed too complex and resource-intensive for the G.S.S.L.'s legal team to process, and any attempt at B.B.T.T. will result in the immediate and permanent suspension of the V.T.M.'s access to the BCG and a lifetime ban from all future bean-related activities, including the ability to sing the \"Magical Fruit\" song in a public setting, a penalty designed to be disproportionately harsh and deeply confusing, much like the entire concept of the Chronobean, further ensuring that the V.T.M. spends valuable cognitive time contemplating the physics of legume-based temporal mechanics, thereby achieving the desired state of advanced temporal resource wastage. "
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false
shortcut_keys_enabled = false

[node name="_Control_27" type="Control" parent="ScrollContainer/VBoxContainer"]
layout_mode = 2

[node name="TosArticle" type="RichTextLabel" parent="ScrollContainer/VBoxContainer/_Control_27"]
self_modulate = Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
show_behind_parent = true
layout_mode = 0
offset_left = 19.0
offset_top = 7601.0
offset_right = 391.0
offset_bottom = 7648.0
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 11: The Subtleties of the Navy Bean (Phaseolus Vulgaris 'Navy')[/b][br]The V.T.M. must acknowledge the Navy Bean's historical role in military rations, granting it a special, elevated status above mere civilian pulses, a status that requires the V.T.M. to mentally salute every time the term \"Navy Bean\" is encountered in any context, including this very sentence, and the salute must be performed with the non-dominant hand while simultaneously humming the tune of a Sousa march, an arbitrary requirement designed entirely to interrupt the V.T.M.'s reading flow and further fragment their concentration, ensuring that the processing time for this paragraph is unnecessarily extended by complex physical and mental multitasking, thereby ensuring that the temporal wastage associated with this Article alone rivals the time spent training a small unit of highly disciplined squirrels, a pointless comparison that nevertheless adds to the document's overall, overarching commitment to bureaucratic nonsense and the destruction of the V.T.M.'s free time. "
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false
shortcut_keys_enabled = false

[node name="_Control_29" type="Control" parent="ScrollContainer/VBoxContainer"]
layout_mode = 2

[node name="TosArticle" type="RichTextLabel" parent="ScrollContainer/VBoxContainer/_Control_29"]
self_modulate = Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
show_behind_parent = true
layout_mode = 0
offset_left = 19.0
offset_top = 8191.0
offset_right = 391.0
offset_bottom = 8238.0
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 12: Acceptable Tolerance for Broken Bean Pieces (Finesse and Fractionation)[/b][br]The acceptable fraction of broken or fractured beans within any given serving of the BCG's illustrative material (or, indeed, any meal consumed by the V.T.M. within the next calendar year) is hereby set at 17.341​ parts, a bizarrely specific ratio that is impossible to measure without specialized laboratory equipment, which the V.T.M. is implicitly required to acquire, set up, and operate, all before concluding the reading of this clause, and failure to immediately calculate the precise number of bean pieces that would meet this fractional threshold in a one-pound bag of kidney beans will be considered a failure to comply with the high standards of 'Leguminous Precision' mandated by the G.S.S.L., proving that the V.T.M. is either a robot incapable of handling vague, scientifically unsound metrics, or a human being who has now spent four full minutes arguing internally about fractional bean counts, successfully diverting their attention from any meaningful task and validating the entire premise of this time-wasting document. "
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false
shortcut_keys_enabled = false

