text = "[b]Article 17: Storage Protocols for Imaginary Lima Beans[/b][br]All imaginary Lima Beans owned or contemplated by the V.T.M. must be stored in a hermetically sealed, hypothetical container maintained at a constant, non-negotiable temperature of 42∘ Kelvin (which is scientifically absurd), and the V.T.M. is solely responsible for mentally tracking and reporting any perceived temperature fluctuations of this imaginary storage facility, a reporting requirement that exists purely to make the V.T.M. perform a pointless, internal check on a fictional scenario based on impossible physical constraints, thereby forcing them to waste cognitive energy on a non-existent task, fulfilling the core mission of the BCG, which prioritizes bureaucratic inefficiency and the depletion of the reader's patience over actual security or common sense, and the penalty for non-compliance is mandatory enrollment in a fictitious 6-week online course titled \"Advanced Lima Bean Thermodynamics.\" "
