text = "[b]Article 18: The Black Bean’s Right to be a Side Dish[/b][br]The V.T.M. must respect the Black Bean’s inherent right to be considered a viable and significant main course component, and not merely a side dish or garnish, and any internal classification of the Black Bean as 'secondary' or 'ancillary' shall be considered a form of 'Legume Marginalization' (L.M.), resulting in a temporary, 60-second self-imposed mental timeout during which the V.T.M. must reflect upon the history of Afro-Caribbean cuisine and the Black Bean's rightful place at the center of the plate, and this punitive reflection period is designed to purposefully interrupt the reading flow at a critical juncture, ensuring maximum frustration and the subsequent, intentional loss of the V.T.M.'s place in the text, forcing them to re-read the last few sentences, thereby doubling the temporal cost of this already excessive paragraph and further cementing the G.S.S.L.'s commitment to extreme, time-intensive contractual enforcement. "
