text = "[b]Article 19: Restrictions on Depicting Beans in Watercolor[/b][br]The V.T.M. is forbidden from depicting any bean, whole or partial, in watercolor, as the medium's inherent translucency is deemed insufficient to capture the profound, starchy complexity and robust texture of the legume, and any such unauthorized artistic endeavor shall be considered a 'Heresy of Hue' (H.H.), resulting in a mandatory fine payable in units of 'One Thousand Wasted Seconds' (1,000 W.S.), which the V.T.M. must immediately pay by deliberately staring blankly at the wall for exactly 16 minutes and 40 seconds, and this clause, existing purely to dictate the V.T.M.'s artistic choices in a medium they may not even use, is a perfect example of the G.S.S.L.'s commitment to hyper-specific, entirely irrelevant regulation designed solely to force the V.T.M. to spend an inordinate amount of time contemplating the legal ramifications of a hypothetical painting, thereby successfully achieving the goal of temporal misallocation through artistic bureaucracy. "
