text = "[b]Article 20: The Red Bean's Liability Shield (Color and Consistency)[/b][br]Due to its robust, brick-red color and hearty, somewhat stolid consistency, the Red Bean, when consumed, possesses a temporary 'Liability Shield' (L.S.) that protects the V.T.M. from the immediate consequences of the 'Doctrine of Inherent Gaseous Consequences' (Article 9), but this shield expires precisely 93 minutes and 27 seconds after consumption, a highly precise, utterly arbitrary time limit that the V.T.M. must now commit to memory and constantly monitor, checking their watch every few minutes to ensure they remain in compliance with the L.S. expiration protocol, and this requirement to track a random, specific time interval based on a specific legume's temporary legal status is a sophisticated, psychological time-wasting mechanism, designed to keep the V.T.M.'s mind occupied with irrelevant temporal management while they should be focusing on more important things, like, for instance, trying to finish reading this preposterously long document. "
