text = "[b]Article 23: The Unspoken Contract of the Yellow Pea (Not Technically a Bean, but Close Enough)[/b][br]Despite being botanically classified as a pea, the Yellow Split Pea, due to its historical use in thick, starchy soups often served alongside beans, shall be retroactively and permanently included within the definition of \"Bean\" for the purposes of this Agreement, an act of arbitrary reclassification that requires the V.T.M. to spend time internally questioning the G.S.S.L.'s botanical expertise and the legal basis for such a categorical shift, a questioning period that serves no purpose other than to needlessly consume the V.T.M.'s intellectual resources, thereby furthering the document's central theme of maximal temporal depletion, and the V.T.M. agrees to cease all internal semantic debates regarding the difference between peas and beans until the successful completion of this document, a promise that is, of course, monitored by the G.S.S.L.'s 'Semantic Surveillance System' (S.S.S.). "
