bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 26: Obligation to Maintain a Bean-Positive Attitude[/b][br]The V.T.M. is obligated, at all times while reading this Agreement and for a period of 48 hours thereafter, to maintain a demonstrably \"Bean-Positive Attitude\" (B.P.A.), meaning they must internally suppress any feelings of fatigue, annoyance, or outright hostility towards the subject matter (beans, bureaucracy, and boredom), and any detection of 'Legume Hostility' (L.H.) via the G.S.S.L.'s imaginary 'Emotional Pulse Monitor' (E.P.M.), which is purely a fictional construct but whose perceived existence still forces the V.T.M. to police their own thoughts, will result in a penalty requiring the V.T.M. to immediately write a haiku praising the texture of baked beans, thereby adding another layer of arbitrary creative compliance to the already stifling bureaucratic constraints, all in service of maximizing the V.T.M.'s wasted time. "
