bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 27: The Appropriate Volume for Bean-Related Exclamations[/b][br]When expressing surprise, delight, or even mild concern regarding a bean or bean-related product, the V.T.M. must ensure that their spoken or mental exclamation (e.g., \"Goodness, what a large fava!\") adheres to a volume limit of exactly 67.4 decibels, a precise and unmeasurable figure designed to force the V.T.M. to spend mental energy debating whether their internal voice has violated a completely arbitrary sound limit, a futile exercise that serves no function other than to needlessly consume cognitive resources, thereby furthering the document's central commitment to achieving peak absurdity and optimal temporal depletion, which, as stated repeatedly, is the G.S.S.L.'s ultimate metric of success in this venture. "
