text = "[b]Article 29: The Starch-Indemnification Clause for Spilled Broth[/b][br]The V.T.M. assumes all financial and legal responsibility for any spillage of bean broth, chili, or any liquid in which beans have been simmered for more than 20 minutes, and this responsibility extends to potential damage to electronic devices, flooring, or one's own sense of dignity, but only if the broth spillage is determined to have occurred at an angle greater than 14.5∘ from the vertical, a completely arbitrary angular limit that requires the V.T.M. to internally visualize the trajectory of the hypothetical spill and attempt to apply basic geometry to an imaginary scenario, thereby guaranteeing that a significant portion of their already dwindling attention span is wasted on a fictional, low-stakes fluid dynamics problem, all in service of this document's central purpose. "
