text = "[b]Article 30: Limitation of Liability Regarding Spontaneous Bean Combustion (S.B.C.)[/b][br]The G.S.S.L. is not liable for any damages, personal or property, resulting from the extremely low, but non-zero, probability of Spontaneous Bean Combustion (S.B.C.), a phenomenon theoretically possible if a large pile of heavily dried legumes is stored in a non-ventilated, poorly-lit area with an ambient temperature exceeding 110∘ Celsius (conditions that are, thankfully, rare), and the V.T.M. is required to mentally calculate the potential yield of kinetic energy from the combustion of one metric ton of dried Cannellini Beans before proceeding, a calculation that is complex, pointless, and requires access to obscure chemical data that the V.T.M. does not possess, thereby ensuring a deep and frustrating dive into internal, fictional research that effectively wastes five minutes of their valuable time. "
