text = "[b]Article 31: The Mandatory Use of Figurative Bean Language[/b][br]The V.T.M. must agree that, for the duration of their session with the BCG, all self-referential statements must use figurative language involving beans; for instance, instead of thinking \"I am tired,\" the V.T.M. must substitute the thought \"My cognitive engine is running on expired pinto broth,\" and this forced, artificial mental substitution is monitored by the S.S.S. (see Article 16), which will trigger a penalty for non-compliance, forcing the V.T.M. to immediately write a 100-word paragraph about the subtle differences between a 'hill of beans' and a 'stack of peas,' thereby ensuring that the V.T.M.'s every thought and subsequent self-correction is a deliberate, time-consuming exercise in utterly pointless, bean-themed cognitive dissonance. "
