bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 39: The Mandatory Pause for Bean Aroma Assessment[/b][br]Upon completion of this paragraph, the V.T.M. is required to take a minimum 45-second pause to mentally simulate the aroma of simmering baked beans, specifically focusing on the interplay between the molasses, mustard, and pork fat, a sensory simulation that must be detailed enough to induce a mild, temporary craving, and this arbitrary olfactory requirement is designed to break the V.T.M.'s focus, force an unscheduled break, and ensure that when they return, they must waste time re-reading the last few sentences to regain context, thereby achieving a cumulative and intentional waste of both time and mental energy, which is the entire point of this document. "
