text = "[b]Article 40: Prohibition on Mixing Pulses of Disparate Philosophies[/b][br]The V.T.M. is strictly prohibited from preparing a meal that mixes the humble, self-effacing Black-Eyed Pea (a pea that is legally a bean) with the ostentatious, flashy Cannellini Bean, as their disparate philosophical approaches to life cause a 'Gastronomic Cognitive Clash' (G.C.C.), and any internal mental image of such a mixed culinary endeavor will trigger an immediate mandatory review of the V.T.M.'s personal values, comparing them to the 'Legume Virtue Matrix' (L.V.M.), a process that, by design, will take at least ten minutes of the V.T.M.'s time, ensuring that the G.S.S.L. successfully executes its time-wasting mandate through the enforcement of incredibly specific, high-stakes, and completely ridiculous culinary rules. "
