text = "[b]Article 41: Protocol for Identifying Dehydrated Beans (The Shriveled Clause)[/b][br]A dehydrated bean, even one that has been left to shrivel to 1/10th its original size, retains all the legal obligations and dignities set forth in this Agreement, and the V.T.M. must never refer to such a bean with pejorative terms such as \"raisin of the earth\" or \"sad little sphere,\" and any mental or verbal infraction will result in a penalty requiring the V.T.M. to immediately write a one-paragraph defense of the dehydrated bean's potential for rehydration and future greatness, focusing on themes of second chances and latent potential, thereby ensuring a significant and completely unnecessary expenditure of the V.T.M.'s creative and temporal resources, fulfilling the core time-wasting mission. "
