text = "[b]Article 42: Appropriate Disposal Methods for Expired Can Labels[/b][br]The V.T.M. must acknowledge that expired bean can labels, particularly those depicting anthropomorphized legumes, must be disposed of via a highly specific, five-step process: (1) Mental Recitation of the Can's Manufacturing Lot Number, (2) Folding the label into a perfect equilateral triangle, (3) A two-minute period of silent reflection on the label designer's artistic choices, (4) Application of a single, non-toxic, water-soluble adhesive sticker, and (5) Placement in a receptacle designated exclusively for 'Historical Paper Artifacts of Leguminous Nature,' a completely fictional receptacle, the contemplation of which forces the V.T.M. to waste valuable seconds debating the logistics of its non-existence, thereby achieving a profound level of bureaucratic, self-inflicted temporal misallocation. "
