text = "[b]Article 43: The Legal Status of Bean Husks and Pod Fragments[/b][br]Bean husks, pod fragments, and all forms of 'Legume Detritus' (L.D.) are considered legally distinct entities from the whole bean, possessing a temporary, transferable micro-liability, and the V.T.M. is required to mentally calculate the potential micro-liability transfer of a single lima bean husk, a calculation which is impossible as the parameters are undefined, thereby forcing the V.T.M. to waste an extended period of time attempting to solve a non-problem with non-data, which is, naturally, the G.S.S.L.'s primary objective: to use overly complex legal phrasing to generate maximum cognitive friction and temporal depletion. "
