bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 45: The Doctrine of Post-Consumption Regret (P.C.R.)[/b][br]The V.T.M. agrees that any feelings of Post-Consumption Regret (P.C.R.) following a bean-heavy meal are the sole property of the G.S.S.L. and may be collected and used for 'Legume Sentiment Analysis' (L.S.A.), which is an entirely fictional process that nonetheless requires the V.T.M. to mentally categorize their feelings of P.C.R. on a scale of 1 to 1,000, with 1,000 being \"profound, life-altering regret,\" and this mandatory self-assessment serves no purpose other than to waste valuable seconds and divert the V.T.M.'s mental energy toward quantifying an abstract emotion, fully satisfying the time-wasting mandate. "
