bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 46: Regulations for Bean-Themed Abstract Art Interpretation[/b][br]Should the V.T.M. encounter any abstract art that they believe to be bean-themed, they must immediately perform a five-minute mental critique of the work, focusing specifically on the artist's use of negative space to imply the absence of beans, which is often more profound than the presence of beans, and this required, pointless artistic contemplation is designed to be a significant, unneeded pause, ensuring that the V.T.M. loses momentum and spends a significant, yet entirely pointless, chunk of time contemplating art theory rather than efficiently completing the Captcha requirement, thereby fulfilling the core mission of maximal, deliberate temporal wastage. "
