text = "[b]Article 47: The Three-Second Rule for Dropped Beans (The Grounding Clause)[/b][br]The standard 'Three-Second Rule' for dropped food is hereby extended to seven (7) seconds for all beans, provided the bean lands on a non-carpeted surface and the V.T.M. can mentally recite the periodic table elements corresponding to the bean's essential mineral content (Potassium, Magnesium, and Iron) before retrieval, a mandatory, multi-step mental challenge that is designed to be time-consuming and cognitively distracting, further solidifying the G.S.S.L.'s commitment to extreme, arbitrary contractual enforcement and maximizing the reader's temporal misallocation through trivial, complex requirements. "
