bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Article 48: Certification of Bean-Related Poetry and Song[/b][br]Any poem, song, or limerick composed by the V.T.M. about beans must first be submitted for a 'Legume Metric Audit' (L.M.A.), which assesses the meter, rhythm, and structural integrity of the artistic work against a 14th-century Tuscan standard that is entirely irrelevant and impossible to meet, and the V.T.M. must spend ten minutes mentally debating the feasibility of their poetic compliance, thereby ensuring a significant and measurable waste of time dedicated to artistic bureaucracy, which is the entire point of this incredibly long and deliberately tedious legal text. "
