text = "[b]Article 49: The Mandatory Pre-Soak Meditation Period[/b][br]Before soaking any dried beans, the V.T.M. must engage in a five-minute 'Pre-Soak Meditation' (P.S.M.), focusing exclusively on the upcoming hydration process and the subtle, physical changes the bean will undergo, a mandatory pause designed to be just long enough to distract the V.T.M. from any meaningful task and force them to re-read the last few sentences, thereby doubling the temporal cost of this already excessive paragraph and further cementing the G.S.S.L.'s commitment to extreme, time-intensive contractual enforcement. "
