text = "[b]Article 50: Prohibition on Naming Pets After Generic Bean Varieties[/b][br]The V.T.M. is strictly prohibited from naming any domestic animal (pet) after a generic bean variety (e.g., \"Pinto,\" \"Kidney,\" or \"Lima\"), and must instead use a highly specific, obscure cultivar name (e.g., \"Hopi Black,\" \"Calypso,\" or \"Yin-Yang Bean\"), and any infraction will result in a mandatory 20-minute mental research period dedicated to finding an acceptable, obscure bean name, thereby ensuring a significant and measurable waste of time dedicated to pointless, niche nomenclature research, fulfilling the core time-wasting mission of this document. "
