text = "[b]Article 53: The Inherent Rights of the Bean Sprouts[/b][br]Bean sprouts, being living entities in an early stage of development, possess an inherent right to 'Germinative Self-Determination' (G.S.D.), and the V.T.M. must mentally respect this right by not consuming any sprout that has not yet reached a minimum length of 1.34 centimeters, an arbitrary, precise measurement that forces the V.T.M. to waste time visualizing and mentally measuring a tiny vegetable, thereby achieving a micro-level of cognitive distraction that, when multiplied by 100 articles, results in the desired total temporal waste. "
