text = "[b]Article 55: The Liability of Overly Enthusiastic Stirring[/b][br]The G.S.S.L. is not responsible for any damage to cookware, wooden spoons, or the V.T.M.'s wrists resulting from 'Overly Enthusiastic Bean Stirring' (O.E.B.S.), defined as any stirring motion that exceeds 120 rotations per minute or involves unnecessary vertical movement, and the V.T.M. must mentally agree to employ a more measured, stoic stirring technique, and this clause, existing purely to regulate a trivial culinary act, is a perfect example of the G.S.S.L.'s commitment to hyper-specific, entirely irrelevant regulation designed solely to force the V.T.M. to spend an inordinate amount of time contemplating the legal ramifications of stirring beans. "
