text = "[b]Article 57: The Proper Pronunciation of \"Phaseolus Vulgaris\"[/b][br]The V.T.M. must mentally pronounce the Latin binomial for the common bean, Phaseolus Vulgaris, correctly on the first attempt, and any internal mispronunciation (e.g., placing the emphasis on the wrong syllable or adding an extra, silent 'H') will trigger a mandatory, 10-minute 'Classical Legume Linguistics Remedial Session' that the V.T.M. must conduct in their head, ensuring a significant and completely unnecessary waste of time dedicated to niche, faux-academic compliance. "
