text = "[b]Article 58: Prohibition on Bean-Based Whispering Campaigns[/b][br]The V.T.M. is strictly prohibited from engaging in any 'Bean-Based Whispering Campaign' (B.B.W.C.), defined as spreading rumors, subtle doubts, or mild negativity about one bean variety (e.g., the Lima Bean) to subtly elevate the status of another (e.g., the Black Bean), as this constitutes 'Legume Market Manipulation,' and the V.T.M. must spend five minutes mentally drafting a press release that equally praises the nutritional merits of all 100 bean varieties, a punitive creative task designed solely to consume their precious time. "
