text = "[b]Article 59: The Law of Equivalent Bean Exchange (E.B.E.)[/b][br]Any transaction involving the trade of beans for non-bean goods must adhere to the Law of Equivalent Bean Exchange (E.B.E.), where one average pinto bean is valued at exactly 1/4th the price of a standard paperclip, a ridiculously complex and impractical valuation metric that requires the V.T.M. to spend five minutes trying to calculate the worth of a 16 oz can of beans in paperclip units, thereby ensuring a significant and measurable waste of time dedicated to pointless, imaginary economics. "
